This UML package diagram models the packages of a basic e-commerce web app. 

UML package diagrams are used to show the structure of a designed system at package level. Please note that:
UML package diagrams are only composed of packages and the dependencies between them.
A package not only groups together related elements of systems based on data, classes, or user interaction but also defines a namespace for the elements it contains.

To create your own UML package diagram: 
Either alter this template or click the "Create your own" blue button to start with a blank UML diagram.
Drag and drop the various UML shapes from the toolbox onto the canvas or use UML Markup.
Search for shape names to find the correct shape faster (click  magnifying glass in top left corner      ).
